    <h2>About Saintstir &copy;</h2><br/>

    <p>Saintstir is a search engine that makes searching for and learning about the
    saints of the Catholic Church fun! Through an easy-to-use explore and search, Saintstir will
    help you to discover facts about your favorite saints, discover saints that you've never
    known (but wish you had), and share your personal stories and prayers with friends.</p>

    <p>Most importantly, you'll learn why each saint is relevant for our modern world, and how our
    saints can teach, guide, and assist us through our journey on Earth.  Saintstir provides an intuitive
    taxonomy on the saints by factoring in life experiences and graces, along with biographical details such as
    historical time periods, to make the saints more accessible to everyone.  We believe that its a saint's
    virtues and personal stories that capture the essence of who they are - and that lies at the heart
    of the saints featured on Saintstir.</p>

    <p>Saintstir is a great site not only to discover saints, but also to share and learn with others.
    Log into Saintstir with your Facebook, Twitter or Google account.
    Add a prayer to the saints and share a story about that saint if (s)he has had a particular impact
    on your life.  Enrich others through your experiences.</p>

    <p>Integrating Saintstir with your website, blog, or app is easy as well.
    Just copy and paste the code links next to each saint to add saint tiles to your site.  If you are
    an app developer, our search and filtering API is available to the public.
    See the <%= link_to "Developer's Guide", page_path('developers') %>

